CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 3 reads: "James Weldon Johnson Camp Model Project - Above are scenes from Camp James Weldon Johnson, situated on Raccoon Creek in foothills of the beautiful Allegehney [Allegheny] mountains just 34 miles from Pittsburg. Some of the children who enjoyed the facilities of the spacious grounds during the past two weeks are pictured...Right: A group of boys and girls enjoy a frolic in the cool lake waters as guards Phillips and Robinson map out a water program for the day."
TitMainTitle: Boys and girls swimming in lake while lifeguards William Phillips and Clarence L. Robinson look on, at Camp Weldon Johnson, Beaver County, Pennsylvania
